nt of a long GRB and a detection of a\nshort GRB every decade. In addition, we expect much more frequent detection of\nGW from GRBs directed away from us, including orphan afterglows. The ultimate\nDECIGO sensitivy should increase the range and enable detecting these signals\nin all models even to high cosmological z.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 22 Feb 2013 21:15:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 14 Mar 2013 19:53:20 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 29 May 2013 20:00:10 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 18 Jun 2013 17:06:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-01-21"}
